description:
I am using version 1.1rc1 of ajc. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a class in a subpackage, for example:
   package subpackage;

   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }

2. Compile the class using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java

